# percolator
**percolator** is a post-processing tool for the Forecasting and Tracking the 
evolution of cloud clusters (ForTraCC) algorithm output.

## Introduction

**Mesoscale convective systems (MCSs)** are massive and complex cloud system that 
generate substantial precipitation and severe weather events worldwide. 
Algorithms such as Forecasting and Tracking the Evolution of Cloud Clusters or **ForTraCC** ([Machado et al., 1998](https://journals.ametsoc.org/view/journals/mwre/126/6/1520-0493_1998_126_1630_lcvomc_2.0.co_2.xml); [Vila et al., 2008](https://journals.ametsoc.org/view/journals/wefo/23/2/2007waf2006121_1.xml)) have proven effective in identifying and tracking MCSs.

ForTraCC characterizes each family of pixel clusters using predefined thresholds,
necessitating a post-decision process to determine whether these families 
represent MCSs or another type of system. 

This package organizes the scripts used in the ForTraCC post-processing to match the criteria defined by SAAG DCG and described in [Prein et al., 2023](https://essopenarchive.org/users/489196/articles/673630-km-scale-simulations-of-mesoscale-convective-systems-mcss-over-south-america-a-feature-tracker-intercomparison) and [Rehbein et al., 2024]().


## ForTraCC Post-Processing Results: Summary of Variables
ForTraCC assume an MCS as a FAMILY of convective systems (CS) along the time. 
This means that multiple convective systems observed over time can be grouped 
together as a single MCS family. 


The resultant dataset (csv file) has the Variables described below:

|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Category          | Variable             | Description                                        |
|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Identification    | ID                   | Unique identifier of the MCSs                      |
|                   | CLASSIF              | Classification of the MCS genesis                  |
|                   | CLA                  | Classification of the MCS cluster                  |
|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Time related      | YEAR                 | Year                                               |
|                   | MONTH                | Month                                              |
|                   | DAY                  | Day                                                |
|                   | HOUR                 | Hour                                               |
|                   | date                 | Date (YYYYMMDDHH)                                  |
|                   | timeUTC              | Coordinated Universal Time (UTC)                   |
|                   | time_zone            | Time zone of the MCS`s center of mass              |
|                   | timeLT               | Local time                                         |
|                   | lifespan             | Total lifespan of the cluster (hours)              |
|                   | phase_size           | Phase calculated based on the *SIZE*               |
|                   | phase_lifespan       | Phase calculated based on the *lifespan*           |
|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Geolocation       | XLAT                 | Latitude coordinate of the cluster center of mass  |
|                   | XLON                 | Longitude coordinate of the cluster center of mass |
|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Kinetics          | VEL                  | Cluster center of mass speed displacement (km/h)   |
|                   | DIR                  | Direction of movement of the cluster               |
|                   | INCLI                | Inclination of the cluster                         |
|                   | ECCE                 | Eccentricity of the cluster                        |
|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Extensions        | SIZE                 | Size of the cluster (pixels)                       |
|                   | DSIZE                | Expansion rate of the cluster (pixels/h)           |
|                   | Tb_SIZE_km2          | Size of the cluster (km2)                          |
|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Radiative         | TMED                 | Mean temperature of the cluster  (K)               |
| properties        | DTMED                | Temperature rate change (K)                        |
|                   | TMIN                 | Minimum temperature of the cluster (K)             |
|                   | DTMIN                | Minimum temperature rate of change (K)             |
|                   | TMIN9                | Minimum temperature of the kernel of 9 pixels (K)  |
|                   | DTMIN9               | DTMIN of the kernel of 9 pixels (K)                |
|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Intensity         | pcp_sum              | Total precipitation below the cloud shield (mm)    |
|                   | pcp_max              | Maximum precipitation below the cloud shield (mm)  |
|                   | pcp_total_vol        | Total volume of precipitation  below the cloud     |
|                   |                      | shield (mm)                                        |
|                   | pcp_total_area       | Total area covered by precipitation below the.     | 
|                   |                      | cloud| shield (km2)                                |
|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Quality control   | MISSINGS             | If original data is corrupted 1, otherwise 0       |
|-------------------|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------|


